early indicated and the text is accompanied by detailed maps. Brief biographical accounts of persons with places named after them as well as an abundance of anecdotes make this a fascinating book for browsers and an invaluable resource for historians.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNames, GeographicalzBritish Columbia. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geography.2bisacsh1 aAkrigg, Helen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311141940440uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485302640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774853026423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774853026/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141940-4  University of British Columbia eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles